investigation.title: Accelerated knowledge discovery from omics data by optimal experimental design
investigation.description: How to design experiments that accelerate knowledge discovery on complex biological landscapes remains a tantalizing question. Here, we present OPEX, an optimal experimental design method to identify informative omics experiments for both experimental space exploration and model training.

project.funding: This work was supported by NSF ABI award 1743101, NSF OCI award 1516695, and XSEDE award TG-BCS180014 for computational resources, and an unrestricted gift from Mars Inc. to I.T.
